               </ab></div></div>
         <div type="translation" source="#irt2009" xml:lang="en">
            <p>a.To our lord Flavius Claudius Constantine, most noble and excellent Caesar <note>all erased</note>. b. To our Lord Flavius Julius Constantius Pius, Felix, always Augustus. </p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>
               <note>a</note> Constantinus II: Erased after damnatio in 340. The omission of the title Augustus is singular, see below. </p>
            <p>
               <note>b</note> Constantius II: Augustus with his brothers, Constantinus and Constans, from Sept. 337</p>
         </div>
